.START 

Norma J. Arnold, 39 years old, was named senior vice president, membership marketing, at the American Express Travel Related Services Co. division.
The appointment is an expansion of her duties as vice president, personal cardmember retention services.
Separately at the division, Steven W. Alesio, 35, was named to the newly created post of senior vice president and general manager of the retail travel network U.S.A. operation.
Mr. Alesio had been vice president, marketing, for travel management services.
American Express also has interests in financial services and publishing. 

